"ဤအပိုင်းတွင် အောက်ပါအကြောင်းအရာကို ရှင်းပြထားသည်။ This is quite simple to implement, with a "
"`setTimeout` or `setInterval` in the statistics service. However, here is the tricky part: if the"
" dashboard is currently being displayed, it should be updated immediately."

#: ../../home/slo/Documents/Projects/odoo19_docs/content/developer/tutorials/discover_js_framework/02_build_a_dashboard.rst:302
msgid ""
"To do that, one can use a `reactive` object: it is just like the proxy returned by `useState`, "
"but not linked to any component. A component can then do a `useState` on it to subscribe to its "
"changes."
msgstr ""
"ဤအပိုင်းတွင် အောက်ပါအကြောင်းအရာကို ရှင်းပြထားသည်။ To do that, one can use a `reactive` object: it"
" is just like the proxy returned by `useState`, but not linked to any component. A component can "
"then do a `useState` on it to subscribe to its changes."

#: ../../home/slo/Documents/Projects/odoo19_docs/content/developer/tutorials/discover_js_framework/02_build_a_dashboard.rst:307
